1
00:00:24,850 --> 00:00:34,430
~Kimi ga haita shiroi iki ga Ima yukkuri kaze ni notte~
<i>*Misty white breaths you exhale, now gently riding on the wind*</i>

2
00:00:34,430 --> 00:00:45,440
~Sora ni ukabu kumo no naka ni sukoshi zutsu kiete yuku~
<i>*Into the clouds in the sky, gradually fading away*</i>

3
00:00:45,440 --> 00:00:55,280
~Toku takai sora no naka de te o nobasu shiroi kumo~
<i>*From up above in the sky white clouds reach down*</i>

4
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:56,690
~Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru~
<i>*To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by*</i>

5
00:00:56,690 --> 00:01:02,080
<i>At the end of the day, when people are rushing home...</i>
~Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru~
<i>*To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by*</i>

6
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:04,890
<i>...That's when my day starts.</i>
~Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru~
<i>*To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by*</i>

7
00:01:04,890 --> 00:01:05,230
~Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru~
<i>*To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by*</i>

8
00:01:06,390 --> 00:01:15,470
~Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne~
<i>*Always seems like a thing of the past*</i>

9
00:01:16,490 --> 00:01:21,180
~Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru~
<i>*Clouds passing over a flowing river*</i>

10
00:01:21,180 --> 00:01:26,850
<i>My business hours start from midnight to 7 am.</i>
~Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru~
<i>*Clouds passing over a flowing river*</i>

11
00:01:26,850 --> 00:01:31,380
<i>People call my eatery
'the late night diner.'</i>

12
00:01:34,696 --> 00:01:39,130
<i>Do customers come? You ask...
There's quite a number who do.</i>

13
00:01:41,602 --> 00:01:49,691
<i>Wabi-Sabi Subs presents:</i>
<b>SHINYA SHOKUDO Season 3</b>
EP 1: "Menchi-Katsu"

14
00:01:50,559 --> 00:01:55,289
"There are three 'fukuro' (bags) that are
important in marriage" speech*...
(*"The 3 Fukuro or Bags of marriage" is a
joke usually mentioned in wedding speeches)

15
00:01:55,289 --> 00:01:57,329
Haven't heard that for a long time.

16
00:01:57,329 --> 00:02:00,929
Yet their marriage will soon turn into
a FUKURO-kouji (dead-end street) anyway.

17
00:02:00,929 --> 00:02:02,529
- Right?
- Right?

18
00:02:02,529 --> 00:02:06,309
Just the other day, you were talking
stuff about pure love, weren't you?

19
00:02:06,309 --> 00:02:08,669
Spoke fondly of one another,
got married...

20
00:02:08,669 --> 00:02:11,479
A few years later, one will cheat
and they'll get a divorce.

21
00:02:11,479 --> 00:02:13,339
Give back the wedding gift!

22
00:02:13,339 --> 00:02:15,399
Let's see... What was that again?

23
00:02:15,399 --> 00:02:18,099
There's "Kannin-BUKURO" (patience),
also, "o-FUKURO" (mother)...

24
00:02:18,099 --> 00:02:20,139
And also... Kinnn~...

25
00:02:20,139 --> 00:02:21,799
Stop with your jokes.

26
00:02:21,799 --> 00:02:24,939
It's "kinchacku-BUKURO" (pay check).
It did sound bad.

27
00:02:24,939 --> 00:02:27,279
Should be "iBUKURO" (stomach), after all.

28
00:02:27,279 --> 00:02:29,499
Thanks for waiting.

29
00:02:30,349 --> 00:02:33,099
Toyama-san, butter rice again?

30
00:02:33,099 --> 00:02:37,069
Since you're a food critic, you should
try other sorts of dishes.

31
00:02:37,069 --> 00:02:41,369
After trying out so many...
you have come to a conclusion. Right?

32
00:02:46,899 --> 00:02:48,339
Welcome.

33
00:02:50,569 --> 00:02:52,139
Good evening.

34
00:02:52,139 --> 00:02:55,069
Oh, I thought it was someone.

35
00:02:55,299 --> 00:02:59,509
Been so long since I had your menchikatsu*
and I've been craving for it.
(*Deep-fried, breaded cutlet)

36
00:02:59,509 --> 00:03:02,809
Been wanting to come here for a long time but...

37
00:03:02,809 --> 00:03:05,799
I had always been coming here
with Taiichan so...

38
00:03:05,799 --> 00:03:09,099
...it feels awkward if I come here alone.

39
00:03:16,339 --> 00:03:19,399
<i>The "Taicchan" she mentioned,
died 8 years ago...</i>

40
00:03:19,399 --> 00:03:21,869
<i>...he was this person's husband.</i>

41
00:03:22,729 --> 00:03:25,069
You see, I finally...

42
00:03:25,069 --> 00:03:27,779
...overtaken Taicchan in age.

43
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:32,249
You wait, okay? I'll make it right away.

44
00:03:58,549 --> 00:04:02,689
Mm! It's delicious!

45
00:04:03,189 --> 00:04:05,849
It's really juicy.

46
00:04:08,029 --> 00:04:10,249
Haven't changed at all, huh?

47
00:04:10,249 --> 00:04:13,159
It's because it's the same recipe.

48
00:04:13,649 --> 00:04:16,519
I was talking about you.

49
00:04:17,219 --> 00:04:19,799
I'm relieved to see your face.

50
00:04:24,199 --> 00:04:27,709
The day before he died...

51
00:04:27,709 --> 00:04:31,729
...he suddenly said he wanted to
eat your menchikatsu...

52
00:04:31,899 --> 00:04:37,309
I told him,
"Then we'll go after you get discharged."

53
00:04:37,309 --> 00:04:41,709
I see. It was indeed
Taicchan's favorite.

54
00:05:10,359 --> 00:05:12,559
Master...

55
00:05:12,779 --> 00:05:15,059
I'm sorry...

56
00:05:16,459 --> 00:05:18,899
You don't have to force yourself...

57
00:05:18,899 --> 00:05:21,159
I'll wrap the menchi for you...

58
00:05:21,599 --> 00:05:24,599
...and make it an offering for Taicchan.

59
00:05:27,459 --> 00:05:31,859
Thank you. I will do so.

60
00:05:33,179 --> 00:05:36,629
That was Kashima Misao, right? The singer.

61
00:05:36,629 --> 00:05:38,309
What!?

62
00:05:38,309 --> 00:05:40,499
At first, I thought she was somebody.

63
00:05:40,499 --> 00:05:43,969
They were a couple who'd often
come here to eat menchi.

64
00:05:43,969 --> 00:05:47,159
Even up til now, when we go to snack bars,
there's always someone singing her song, right?

65
00:05:47,159 --> 00:05:49,559
~It's fine, it's okay...~

66
00:05:49,559 --> 00:05:51,849
~Don't say anything~

67
00:05:51,849 --> 00:05:55,379
That's right. "Don't Say Anything".
I memorized the chords to that song.

68
00:05:55,379 --> 00:05:57,589
That was a classic.

69
00:05:58,159 --> 00:06:02,309
"Taicchan"? Was he Tachibana Taizo?

70
00:06:02,309 --> 00:06:07,229
Oh! They were known as the songwriting husband
and the singing wife, right?

71
00:06:07,229 --> 00:06:10,349
Come to think about it,
there was such a couple.

72
00:06:10,349 --> 00:06:15,519
She stopped singing after her husband died.

73
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:20,379
Sometimes she'd be featured in those "What happened
now to that person" articles in gossip magazines...

74
00:06:20,379 --> 00:06:24,279
Most of them say she has firmly shut
herself up inside her house.

75
00:06:24,449 --> 00:06:26,419
Since she loved him so much, huh?

76
00:06:26,849 --> 00:06:32,739
Me too. I want to get married to a person who'll
always think of just me even when I'm gone.

77
00:06:32,739 --> 00:06:35,069
My wife is different.

78
00:06:35,069 --> 00:06:39,089
If I die, she's probably
gonna burst into cheers.

79
00:06:40,079 --> 00:06:42,099
Master, I'd like some menchi too.

80
00:06:42,099 --> 00:06:43,289
Sure thing.

81
00:06:43,489 --> 00:06:47,139
We've got some karaoke rooms available.
How about it please?

82
00:06:47,139 --> 00:06:49,979
How about it, ma'am? Would you like to try?

83
00:06:49,979 --> 00:06:54,419
We're having "Those Classics" promo now...
featuring Kashima Misao songs.

84
00:06:54,419 --> 00:06:58,219
You can have your own personal playlist.
Would you like to take this opportunity to sing?

85
00:06:58,219 --> 00:06:59,799
How about it?

86
00:07:04,719 --> 00:07:06,719
Welcome.

87
00:07:17,039 --> 00:07:20,989
One butter rice.
Oh, on second thought...

88
00:07:20,989 --> 00:07:23,019
Can you give me cold liquor?

89
00:07:23,019 --> 00:07:25,019
Sure thing.

90
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:35,019
My wife has fallen ill.

91
00:07:36,809 --> 00:07:39,279
She's in the hospital right now.

92
00:07:40,489 --> 00:07:42,639
It's cancer.

93
00:07:43,659 --> 00:07:47,759
She had surgery but I wonder
what's gonna happen...

94
00:07:50,539 --> 00:07:54,139
Whatever I eat, I can't taste anything.

95
00:07:54,469 --> 00:07:58,189
It's problematic considering I'm a food critic.

96
00:08:03,409 --> 00:08:07,409
The missus is a bad cook, you see.

97
00:08:08,609 --> 00:08:14,359
So I walked around, looking
for delicious food to eat...

98
00:08:14,359 --> 00:08:19,259
Before I knew it, I came to be
called a food critic.

99
00:08:20,979 --> 00:08:26,339
But I guess the wife's bad cooking
is the tastiest after all.

100
00:08:31,599 --> 00:08:34,069
I bought tissues yesterday...

101
00:08:36,139 --> 00:08:39,859
Oh! I forgot the nail trimmer.

102
00:08:39,859 --> 00:08:42,049
I'll bring it tomorrow.

103
00:08:42,859 --> 00:08:47,049
Say, there's a tree outside the window, right?

104
00:08:48,439 --> 00:08:53,599
It feels like by the time all the leaves
have fallen, I'll be dead by then.

105
00:08:53,599 --> 00:08:55,759
Don't say such nonsensical things.

106
00:08:56,359 --> 00:09:00,779
Just kidding. Wanted to say such things
if I get to be hospitalized.

107
00:09:00,779 --> 00:09:03,029
Come on now.

108
00:09:03,599 --> 00:09:05,999
I've become scared somehow.

109
00:09:08,559 --> 00:09:12,179
After you get discharged,
let's go out and eat something good.

110
00:09:12,609 --> 00:09:15,969
Let's go to a stylish trattoria in Azabu.

111
00:09:16,379 --> 00:09:18,579
They even have customers coming from Sicily.

112
00:09:20,139 --> 00:09:22,789
Am I gonna be discharged?

113
00:09:23,219 --> 00:09:27,169
The doctor too have said so.

114
00:09:27,169 --> 00:09:29,129
But...

115
00:09:30,999 --> 00:09:33,899
Is there anything you want?

116
00:09:35,669 --> 00:09:37,559
Say whatever whim you like.

117
00:09:40,179 --> 00:09:44,439
Well... there's a song I want to hear.

118
00:09:44,749 --> 00:09:46,529
There's none?

119
00:09:46,779 --> 00:09:48,059
None.

120
00:09:48,059 --> 00:09:51,159
Sorry but it's out of print.

121
00:10:02,529 --> 00:10:12,404
["Don't Say Anything"
Words and Music: Tachibana Taizo]

122
00:10:19,059 --> 00:10:26,959
~Each time I'm nestled in your arms~

123
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:35,059
~I can hear the sound of your heart~

124
00:10:35,509 --> 00:10:37,959
~Wo--...

125
00:10:47,069 --> 00:10:49,119
Excuse me.

126
00:10:58,789 --> 00:11:00,999
Please take your time.

127
00:11:14,319 --> 00:11:15,629
Ah, oww...

128
00:11:15,629 --> 00:11:18,329
Sorry! Are you okay?

129
00:11:25,419 --> 00:11:27,419
Ka-Kashima-san...?

130
00:11:32,689 --> 00:11:36,489
But... why were you at a karaoke place?

131
00:11:37,569 --> 00:11:40,489
Actually, you see...

132
00:11:40,489 --> 00:11:44,319
...I haven't seen myself sing.

133
00:11:44,319 --> 00:11:48,099
As long as Taicchan watched me sing,
that was enough for me.

134
00:11:48,389 --> 00:11:54,061
But when I saw myself in the videos,
is that really me?

135
00:11:54,342 --> 00:11:57,239
I was like "So that's how I sang".

136
00:11:58,009 --> 00:12:01,539
And then stuff like the heat of the spotlight...

137
00:12:01,539 --> 00:12:06,049
...the thickness of the microphone,
I suddenly remembered a lot of things.

138
00:12:06,229 --> 00:12:10,379
So then did you sing?
Along with your old self.

139
00:12:10,509 --> 00:12:11,789
No.

140
00:12:14,089 --> 00:12:16,759
You're not gonna sing anymore?

141
00:12:18,909 --> 00:12:24,509
It's true that people who wish
to hear me sing are gone.

142
00:12:26,379 --> 00:12:34,045
You know.... my wife
is in the hospital.

143
00:12:34,584 --> 00:12:37,451
She's a bit younger than me...

144
00:12:38,009 --> 00:12:42,229
I intend to take care of her but...

145
00:12:43,762 --> 00:12:46,624
At any rate, I wanted to do something for her...

146
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:51,069
...but I can't do anything.

147
00:12:52,768 --> 00:12:55,428
Just the other day...

148
00:12:56,554 --> 00:12:58,944
...she told me she wants to hear a song.

149
00:13:02,334 --> 00:13:06,284
She said she wants to hear
Kashima Misao's "Don't Say Anything".

150
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:10,161
I didn't know that she has a favorite song.

151
00:13:10,186 --> 00:13:14,026
No, not just that. There might be many
other things I wasn't aware of.

152
00:13:15,481 --> 00:13:18,341
Misao-san, please...

153
00:13:18,989 --> 00:13:21,979
Could you sing "Don't Say Anything" once again...

154
00:13:22,079 --> 00:13:23,979
For my wife.

155
00:13:25,703 --> 00:13:28,743
I'm sorry but I can't.

156
00:13:29,114 --> 00:13:32,327
I know I am being rude
by begging but...

157
00:13:32,352 --> 00:13:34,452
She wishes to hear it.

158
00:13:36,759 --> 00:13:38,199
I can't.

159
00:13:38,199 --> 00:13:40,049
But why?

160
00:13:40,489 --> 00:13:45,829
It's not okay! Telling me to sing
in order to encourage your wife.

161
00:13:45,829 --> 00:13:52,439
You see, I promised in front
of Taicchan's coffin...

162
00:13:52,439 --> 00:13:56,139
"I'm not gonna sing for people anymore!"

163
00:14:30,112 --> 00:14:31,662
I'm sorry.

164
00:14:32,912 --> 00:14:34,392
What for?

165
00:14:34,842 --> 00:14:39,142
Well, apparently, CDs of the song
are out of print.

166
00:14:43,862 --> 00:14:45,602
I knew.

167
00:14:48,062 --> 00:14:50,662
I knew that what I said was a whim.

168
00:15:01,007 --> 00:15:03,007
Don't cry.

169
00:15:04,632 --> 00:15:06,932
I've no reason to cry.

170
00:15:12,082 --> 00:15:12,902
Welcome.

171
00:15:12,902 --> 00:15:17,092
Master, can you reserve the place for me
on the 17th? Are those hours okay with you?

172
00:15:17,092 --> 00:15:19,332
Sure but what's up?

173
00:15:19,332 --> 00:15:23,682
My wife's discharge had been decided.
And we're gonna celebrate a bit.

174
00:15:23,682 --> 00:15:26,052
Glad to hear it. Congratulations.

175
00:15:26,052 --> 00:15:30,992
Yeah well. From here on...
I'll leave it to you then.

176
00:15:48,012 --> 00:15:50,012
Here you go.

177
00:15:51,612 --> 00:15:56,242
You know, Master. I don't cry anymore
when I eat menchi.

178
00:15:56,322 --> 00:15:57,782
Yeah.

179
00:15:58,055 --> 00:16:01,392
I feel troubled each time you cry.

180
00:16:01,392 --> 00:16:03,234
Suppose so.

181
00:16:03,641 --> 00:16:09,622
Misao-san. You still don't want to sing?

182
00:16:11,952 --> 00:16:15,182
When Taicchan was dying...

183
00:16:15,182 --> 00:16:18,852
I was singing love songs on stage.

184
00:16:18,852 --> 00:16:22,272
If I gave up singing and became
an ordinary woman much earlier...

185
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:26,642
...I wonder if I could have
been a better wife to him?

186
00:16:26,862 --> 00:16:37,832
I wonder if Taicchan loved you more for being
a singer than an ordinary woman.

187
00:16:50,652 --> 00:16:53,802
I came after hearing
from Master of "Meshi-ya".

188
00:16:54,572 --> 00:16:56,832
Uh... Eh?

189
00:16:57,622 --> 00:17:00,012
Oh... Kashima-san?

190
00:17:07,202 --> 00:17:11,822
I thought it's better to speak
to you directly.

191
00:17:12,212 --> 00:17:15,462
I'm really sorry that I can't sing.

192
00:17:15,462 --> 00:17:19,182
Don't be. It's I who should apologize.

193
00:17:19,182 --> 00:17:22,432
Asking my husband for
something that can't be done.

194
00:17:23,022 --> 00:17:27,342
But because that person did a silly thing...

195
00:17:27,342 --> 00:17:30,182
I got to meet you.

196
00:17:31,172 --> 00:17:34,772
Thank you for coming.

197
00:17:39,882 --> 00:17:41,882
Misao-san.

198
00:17:44,325 --> 00:17:46,735
If you ever sing again...

199
00:17:47,492 --> 00:17:52,782
...instead for others,
please sing for yourself.

200
00:18:08,612 --> 00:18:14,022
You didn't tell me words like
you loved me but...

201
00:18:14,022 --> 00:18:17,482
Your songs were your
love letters to me, right?

202
00:18:18,462 --> 00:18:23,992
I got plenty of love letters from you.

203
00:18:25,112 --> 00:18:30,162
But I feel scared and lonely...

204
00:18:30,472 --> 00:18:32,972
I can't bring myself to "reread" them.

205
00:18:35,392 --> 00:18:42,412
So unfair. When I let myself
loved you so much...

206
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:44,612
...you died on me.

207
00:18:47,082 --> 00:18:49,122
You're so unfair.

208
00:18:58,047 --> 00:19:02,192
<i>That day, after considering the physical
condition of Toyama's wife...</i>

209
00:19:02,192 --> 00:19:05,272
<i>...I decided to open the shop
as early as possible.</i>

210
00:19:05,272 --> 00:19:08,842
- It's delicious! Yum!
- Is that good?

211
00:19:08,842 --> 00:19:12,412
- You want something?
- It's good. Thanks.

212
00:19:12,412 --> 00:19:15,052
- Gimme some daikon.
- Daikon? - Oh, daikon! Here...

213
00:19:15,052 --> 00:19:18,112
Well... it's time for the song.

214
00:19:18,612 --> 00:19:21,232
Yes! We've been waiting!

215
00:19:21,382 --> 00:19:25,372
A once-in-lifetime love.
A love that endures.

216
00:19:25,372 --> 00:19:27,822
To be sung by a 3 star-voice...

217
00:19:27,822 --> 00:19:31,612
...please listen to "Don't Say anything".

218
00:19:47,812 --> 00:19:56,392
~Each time I'm nestled in your arms...~

219
00:19:56,392 --> 00:20:04,612
~I can hear the sound of your heart~

220
00:20:04,612 --> 00:20:12,952
~Words are not always enough~

221
00:20:12,952 --> 00:20:21,412
~You can't convey everything~

222
00:20:21,412 --> 00:20:29,522
~That is why, you've always
been the way you are~

223
00:20:29,522 --> 00:20:37,792
~Quiet and shy~

224
00:20:37,792 --> 00:20:45,192
~I like that about you~

225
00:20:45,192 --> 00:20:50,342
~Whisper in my ear~

226
00:20:50,342 --> 00:20:53,762
~The song of love~

227
00:20:53,762 --> 00:21:02,402
~It's fine, it's okay~

228
00:21:02,402 --> 00:21:10,142
~Don't say anything~

229
00:21:10,142 --> 00:21:18,722
~It's fine, it's okay~

230
00:21:18,722 --> 00:21:28,332
~Don't say anything~

231
00:21:31,682 --> 00:21:43,482
~Don't say anything~

232
00:21:50,282 --> 00:21:54,152
Thank you for listening!

233
00:21:59,312 --> 00:22:01,412
That was nice.

234
00:22:03,512 --> 00:22:07,242
Master, give me menchi!

235
00:22:07,902 --> 00:22:09,552
Sure thing.

236
00:22:14,322 --> 00:22:20,022
<i>Seems these two people
have brought Misao-san back to life.</i>

237
00:22:26,072 --> 00:22:31,872
The percentage of meat is around
70% beef and 30% pork.

238
00:22:33,282 --> 00:22:37,962
Use plenty of coarse panko (breadcrumbs).

239
00:22:37,962 --> 00:22:40,002
Yeah, yeah.

240
00:22:40,002 --> 00:22:42,452
This is nerve-racking.

241
00:22:42,452 --> 00:22:47,672
To avoid splattering the oil,
gently put it in...

242
00:22:47,672 --> 00:22:49,642
What's the temperature of the oil?

243
00:22:49,642 --> 00:22:51,162
Huh? I dunno.

244
00:22:51,162 --> 00:22:53,262
Ah! The menchi's gonna explode.

245
00:22:53,692 --> 00:22:55,992
Ah, oww! Hot!

246
00:22:55,992 --> 00:23:01,802
~Hohoende kureta kao mo okottakao mo~
<i>*Even if it's laughing or mad*</i>

247
00:23:01,802 --> 00:23:07,712
~Itoshikute shikatanakatta yo~
<i>*I adore your face, can't be helped*</i>

248
00:23:07,712 --> 00:23:11,982
~Kimi no koto ga sukida yo~
<i>*I love you*</i>

249
00:23:11,982 --> 00:23:19,982
~Korekara mo zutto kimi o dakishimetai~
<i>*I want to hold you in my arms now and forever*</i>

250
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:28,562
~Kimi o tsuyoku dakishimetai~
<i>*I want to hold you tightly in my arms*</i>

